question: In which nation "Guaniguanico Mountain Range" is located?
explanation: Guaniguanico Mountain Range is a mountain range located in western Cuba. It is also known as Cordillera de Guaniguanico. The highest peak of this range is Pan de Guajaibon. It houses Sierra del Rosario and Sierra de Los Organos mountains and the San Diego River which divides the two. It also houses the Vinales Valley.
